<project xml:id="cool-areaConUnLadoDesconocido" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Área con un lado desconocido</title>

<statement>
  <p>Encuentra el área de la figura. Explica o muestra tu razonamiento.</p>
  <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-151026">
        <shortdescription>Polígono verde en T con medidas de lados en centímetros.</shortdescription>
      </image>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>42 sq cm. Sample response: I found the area of the top rectangle to be 30 sq cm because <m>3 \times 10 = 30</m>. Then I found the missing side length to be 6 cm by subtracting 3 cm and 1 cm from 10 cm because opposite side lengths are equal in a rectangle. Then I found the area of the smaller rectangle on the bottom to be <m>2 \times 6</m>, which is 12 sq cm. Then I added <m>30 + 12</m> to get 42 sq cm.</p>
  </solution>


